{"pageProps":{"note":{"id":"lsdowxbs8rosa1s8qxolpe3","title":"Dual Boot Timezone","desc":"","updated":1662141275866,"created":1662140885186,"custom":{},"fname":"linux.tips.dual-boot-timezone","type":"note","vault":{"fsPath":".","selfContained":true,"name":"docs"},"contentHash":"4f07b5c9aabb220dbbf126547fc87907","links":[],"anchors":{"fix-wrong-time-dual-boot-between-ubuntu--windows":{"type":"header","text":"Fix wrong time dual boot between Ubuntu & Windows","value":"fix-wrong-time-dual-boot-between-ubuntu--windows","line":8,"column":0,"depth":1},"explain":{"type":"header","text":"Explain","value":"explain","line":18,"column":0,"depth":2}},"children":[],"parent":"ja38h1kpr0pizpzgpifp4nu","data":{}},"body":"<h1 id=\"dual-boot-timezone\">Dual Boot Timezone<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#dual-boot-timezone\"></a></h1>\n<h1 id=\"fix-wrong-time-dual-boot-between-ubuntu--windows\">Fix wrong time dual boot between Ubuntu &#x26; Windows<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#fix-wrong-time-dual-boot-between-ubuntu--windows\"></a></h1>\n<blockquote>\n<p><a href=\"https://itsfoss.com/wrong-time-dual-boot/\">https://itsfoss.com/wrong-time-dual-boot/</a></p>\n</blockquote>\n<pre><code>timedatectl set-local-rtc 1\n</code></pre>\n<p>=> Update the Ubuntu clock to use the local time for the hardware clock (RTC)</p>\n<h2 id=\"explain\">Explain<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#explain\"></a></h2>\n<ul>\n<li>A computer has 2 clocks: hardware &#x26; system\n<ul>\n<li>hardware clock == RTC clock == CMOS/BIOS clock == motherboard's clock</li>\n<li>system clock: operating system clock</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Linux assumes the hardware clock is <strong>the UTC</strong> </li>\n<li>Windows assumes the hardware clock is <strong>the local time</strong></li>\n</ul>","noteIndex":{"id":"xfkxbponh0sohobo6pual15","title":"Root","desc":"","updated":1668137379975,"created":1663481872547,"custom":{"nav_order"